fields.value: A self-motivated and independent Computer Engineer with 2+ year of professional and 2+ years of non-professional experience in core Python, JavaScript, R and different tech stacks in software development, machine learning, data science, and clinical domain.

fields.bullet: Redesigned the existing WordPress website and wrote requirements to migrate to Python Django based server-client application.
Designed all the backends and data models for the application, and assigned tasks to individual developers
Mostly worked on the backend functionality, and data validation, integrity, and security of the application
Implemented Esewa online payment gateway API
Integrated both the backends and frontends, and managed GitHub repository
Defined coding convention and git workflows to be used in organization which improved productivity, readability, maintainability, and the quality

Designed and developed core features of a sophisticated data analytics and visualization tool; creating CDISC frequency count, and summary statistics reports, deriving variable,  and dataset from a da

Wrote several optimized SQL queries for SQLite database operations
Assisted in different recruitments by shortlisting and taking the technical interviews of several applicants
Performed benchmarks for different requirements, and libraries
Led a team of 10 developers to develop RESTful application on Django, R, and React ecosystem (react JS, redux JS, redux-thunk, etc).
Designed, and documented architecture, data models, and end points specification of the applications using visio, draw.io, and confluence
Actively worked as a full-stack developer, reviewed other developers' code, managed bitbucket repositories, and documented the work
Mainly worked in desktop, and web based RESTful data analytics, Visualization and reporting applications for pharmaceutical industry
Closely worked with client from US, for requirement analysis, system design, and strategic planning
Set up the job descriptions/requirements, and conducted technical interviews for different openings in the organization
Performed POC, feasibility tests, and benchmarks for different requirements, libraries, and frameworks
